msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:19
msgid "race^Animals"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The wildlife is divided into the magical monsters and the non magical "
"animals. Many animals have evolved an immense strenght or agility to make up "
"for their lacking magical properties. There is no clear line between those "
"two categories as many beasts have a small amount of magic in them, but not "
"enough to show. Wild creatures can pose a threat to travellers, but tamed "
"ones are of great use."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:26
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:28
msgid "race^Aquana"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:27
msgid "race+female^Aquana"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:29
msgid ""
"\n"
"<header>text='Appearance'</header>\n"
"Aquana descended from mermen and Rashky. Though this would technically make "
"the Rashy, they see themself as individual race. Depending on the location "
"they live in their appearance can vary greatly.\n"
"Near their capital, Atlantis, most have a blue, scaly skin and green hair. "
"Their face has some features of a fish and some may even have gills. Aquana "
"living distant from their capital usually look more like humans.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Geography'</header>\n"
"Their capital is located on an island in a gulf on the eastern continent. Its"
" enormous size stretches over the whole island and parts of it reaches into "
"the ocean.\n"
"The country spreads from the capital to the desert in the south-east. Near "
"the main trading routes are many big and rich cities and smaller villages are"
" scattered throughout the land. \n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Culture'</header>\n"
"Aquanas have a large number of merchants, which resulted in a very rich "
"country. In the past they fought many wars against Elyser, Ssrah and Vixens. "
"After allying with Elysys and the Trarashy they life mostly in peace, aside "
"from raids of Marashy and Vixens.\n"
"Their usual trade partner are the Sabana in the southern desert and the "
"Trarashy."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:47
msgid "race^Darkelf"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:48
msgid "race+female^Darkelf"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:49
msgid "race^Darkelves"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:51
msgid ""
"After the invasions of humans on the western continent, the noble elf race "
"came also in contact with more sinnister individuals. Necromancers had come "
"into their forests and cities to teach their arts to anyone who listened, and"
" to kill the ones who didn't. With their long lifespan Elves are in no need "
"for resurrection spells, but some saw a chance to come to power. When the "
"high council saw the rising numbers of black mages they feared an uprising "
"and called for an inquisition.\n"
"The Elves forced all dark sorceres and the ones who sided with them to flee "
"from their land. The exiles called themselves Darkelves and found a new home "
"in inhospitable swamps, caves and dangerous woods. Through generations they "
"adapted to the new lands. Their eyes can see better in the dark and their "
"hair has lost its colour and has become shiny white. Most have a darker skin "
"than the pale Elyser and Woodelves, though it's unknown whether this change "
"occurred because of dark magic or through natural means."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:61
msgid "race^Dwarf (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:62
msgid "race+female^Dwarf (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:63
msgid "race^Dwarves (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:64
msgid ""
"The dwarves are a reclusive race and keep to Mountains, caves and hills. "
"While they keep neutral in war, they don't mind trading with their "
"neighbours. To outsiders they are mostly known for their miners, blacksmiths,"
" merchants and warriors, but when visited, a far deeper culture can be "
"unraveled.\n"
"\n"
"Dwarves are of small stature by human measure, but they are by no means "
"fragile. Their warriors, tough and powerful are both feared and respected "
"throughout the continent for their prowess in battle. In addition, dwarves "
"are known for their calculating intellects and superb craftsmanship. Dwarven "
"smiths are renowned for their deadly weapons and heavy armor. Their "
"intelligence and natural inquisitiveness has also made them the most "
"technically advanced race on the continent.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"<header>text='Mountain Dwarves'</header>\n"
"The most typical dwarves live in high mountains and burry into deep caves "
"from there. Not only do they posses the best blacksmiths, but they also hord "
"a unique kind of magic with their rune smiths and elementarists.\n"
"\n"
"While powerful in their home, their lack of allies, as well as the natural "
"attributes of dwarves, have given them no option to expand their territory "
"beyond mountain range. Though their warmachines could potentially turn a "
"fight on flat terrain, the dwarves try to keep that knowledge for themselve "
"and don't want to risk it falling into enemy hands.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Forest Dwarves'</header>\n"
"Forest Dwarves, sometimes also called Hills Dwarves, are outcasts of the "
"'main' society. Whether they were driven out or made the choice themselve in "
"serach of adventure and profit, they now have to live outside of the "
"mountains and caves of their homeland. Instead they settled on smaller hills "
"and live of nearby woods, by selling lumber directly or using their expert "
"craftsmanship to make art, toys and weapons.\n"
"\n"
"The live on the surface has made them more open to other races and many "
"dwarvish settlements have made friends with gnomes and giants.\n"
"\n"
"Over time these Dwarves adapted to the surface. They tend to be faster than "
"their undergound cousins.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Deep Dwarves'</header>\n"
"The least known kind of dwarves lives deep under the earth. Hardy anyone has "
"seen them, or survived an encounter, since they are hostile to outsiders.\n"
""
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:91
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:93
msgid "race^Elyser"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:92
msgid "race+female^Elyser"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:94
msgid ""
"Elyser are decendants of Woodelf tribes in the western continent. After they "
"had build their capital, Elysys, they gradually conquered surrounding lands. "
"The country is rules by the High Lord of Elysys and his small council. Elyser"
" Elves are used to the city life and not as connected to nature as their "
"ancestors. They are allied with Trarashy and Aquanas, though the Elysyans try"
" to avoid conflict by hiding in their secure capital."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:103
msgid "race^Giant"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:104
msgid "race+female^Giant"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:105
msgid "race^Giants"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:106
msgid ""
"On the first sight, giants don't seem to be related to dwarves, but they "
"actually have the same ancestors. Giants are far bigger and stronger than "
"dwarves, even more than most trolls. While not unintellegent, they are often "
"described as clumsy."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:115
msgid "race^Gnome"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:116
msgid "race+female^Gnome"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:117
msgid "race^Gnomes"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:118
msgid ""
"Gnomes are smaller and more feeble than dwarves. They often live in forests "
"and posses Magic similar to fairies. Their origin is unclear, though it is "
"suspected they are related to either dwarves or fairies."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:127
msgid "race^Human (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:128
msgid "race+female^Human (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:129
msgid "race^Humans (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:130
msgid ""
" The human realms are mostly on the eastern continent, but there are humans "
"and human-like species all over the world.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Chevalier'</header>\n"
"The Chevalier have a well trained and equipped army. Their country is divided"
" into many smaller principalities, who seem to be in constant struggle over "
"power. Chevalier don't practice magic, but have a better understanding of "
"herbs and potions. They have the most skilled blacksmiths of the human realm,"
" though only few can afford the tough armors.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Dardo'</header>\n"
"The Dardos are living onfthe south of the human realm. Their light cavalery "
"is perfect for roaming the wide planes and the great number of infantymen can"
" defend the empire against its enemies.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Luz'</header>\n"
"Originaly the Luz army was created to defend the Highpriest, the head of the "
"human religion. Over many generations the Highpriests increased their power "
"and are now leader of their own state. The Lucian exclude themself from war, "
"though they posses a small force of elite soldiers in case of an invasion.\n"
"Independent from the Highpriest are the Inquisition. They are sworn to "
"protect the religion and the laws given by the Highpriest, but can act on "
"their own accord. The Inquisition controls facilities all over the human "
"realm and can act as judge and executioner.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Regis'</header>\n"
"The Regis are united under one king. He commands the nobility, who rule over "
"the local population. Their army is mostly buid of smallfolk, guided by the "
"better trained aristrocrats. Unlike most other human nations, the Regis "
"accept Magic and have an academy to train them.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Free Folk'</header>\n"
"There are many humans scattered throughout the world. They don't have a "
"single leader, but instead are divided into many different tribes. Noteworthy"
" groups are the Outlaws, Mountaintribes and Forestfolks.\n"
""
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_rashy
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:154
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:156
msgid "race^Rashy"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_rashy
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:155
msgid "race+female^Rashy"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_rashy
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:157
msgid ""
"The Rashy are not a single race. Instead their realm is inhabited by all "
"possible hybrid creatures. The largest number descendet from humans, elves "
"and aquanas, but even dragons are possible ancestors. There is one thing all "
"Rashy have in common: At least one of their ancestors was a Rashky.\n"
"Rashkys are ancient creatures, with a magic strong enough to create or "
"destroy worlds. Though they are all gone now and the magic has grown weaker "
"in every generation of their descendants, the  Rashy are still the strongest "
"mages in the world.\n"
"Rashys can look very differently, depending on their bloodline. Most look "
"like humans, a bit shorter maybe and with a pale, blueish skin. While the "
"Rashky genes make them magic resistant, the combination of so many different "
"species have left them weak against physical attacks.\n"
"\n"
"(Note: Rashky and Rashy are very differnt. Rashky are shapeshifters with near"
" godlike power. The older Rashy generations still possesed a lot of power and"
" can have children with most humanoids. Through many generations almost all "
"species on the western continent have Rashky genes. Newer generations usually"
" don't have much power. Their ancestry has a big influence on their traits.)\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Trarashy'</header>\n"
"Trarashy aren't very longelively. The Rashky genes have enabled them to breed"
" with every species, but this has left them susceptible to almost all "
"diseases. Their life expectancy of a normal citizen is about 30 years. "
"Trarashy Mages on the other hand are powerful enough to live far longer. Some"
" specimen reached an age above 1000 years.\n"
"Their population consists mostly of farmers and only a few are chosen to "
"study magic in the great libraries. The strong and wise mages, loath "
"violence, which leaves the Trarashy as a fairly peaceful species. Over time "
"they have build a close friendship with the neighboring countries, Elysys and"
" Aquana.\n"
"Trarashy are tolerant to most religions and cultures. Most pray to gods and "
"goddesses of nature or to their ancestors.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Marashy'</header>\n"
"The Trarashy choose their mages carefully, but even the best eyes can miss a "
"foul apple. Marashys originated from corrupt sorcerers, who choose to use "
"their power to conquer the Trarashys. Though they never fully succeeded, they"
" managed to build their own country in the north. From time to time they "
"raise an army to raid Trarashy lands and try to plunder the Rashky libraries "
"for secret knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Dragoon'</header>\n"
"There is a small state located in the northern mountains of the west "
"continent, which inhabits a Rashy folk descendet from Dragons. They look like"
" humanoids with a red scaly skin and are stronger than most other Rashys. "
"Dragoons have no allies, but often help Trarashy in times of war.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='Sabana'</header>\n"
"Sabana are an independent Rashy desertfolk. They have a few cities near the "
"ocean, though many tribes travel as nomads through the sands. Their only "
"allies are their trading partners, the Aquanas, and their only enemy is the "
"harsh desert itself.\n"
""
msgstr ""

