msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_vixen
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:206
msgid ""
"Vixens are humanoids with fox-like features. They live on a group of islands "
"near the western continent. Their society is dominated by women and the few "
"males, often just called foxes, are rarely seen.\n"
"The Amazons were at war with the Ssrah for a long time, but made an alliance "
"when they had to fight Aquana, Trarashy and Elyser."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:215
msgid "race^Undead (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:216
msgid "race+female^Undead (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:217
msgid "race+plural^Undead (Rashy Era)"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\races.cfg:218
msgid ""
"Undead are not really a single race of creatures, although often treated as "
"such. Most ordinary creatures can, by a sufficiently skilled necromancer, be "
"reanimated into constructs of varying character — resurrection of the "
"physical form often results in a minion that obeys its master without "
"question, while manifestation of a soul usually produces a servant with at "
"least a modicum of thought. A great mystery of necromancy is how these "
"constructs are sustained and controlled without continuous effort from the "
"necromancer. Most dark magi do not provide constant attention or maintenance "
"to their creations, instead allowing them a small degree of independence to "
"function autonomously in line with the provided commands. However, when left "
"unchecked, some undead gain enough sovereignty to break free from and even "
"turn on their masters. Accordingly, while even lesser undead require periodic"
" maintenance, this is especially true for more powerful undead, particularly "
"greater spirits or death knights, who possess a high degree of inherent will."
" In these cases, necromancy becomes a battle of resolve between mage and "
"minion. The necromancer must maintain a delicate balance between control over"
" their servants and allotting them free will — the source of their individual"
" powers.\n"
"\n"
"<header>text='history'</header>\t\t\n"
"The history of Necromancy began with some enterprising Chevalier Doctors. "
"Experiments of healing magic on dead bodies eventually resulted in one being "
"overshoot with magical energy. This reanimated corpse was a poor imitation of"
" live however and their scientific advancement neither resulted in eternal "
"live, nor was it praised by their fellow humans.\n"
"\n"
"Necromacy was banned in the human realms as soon as the abominations they "
"created were seen by the public and the once prestigious doctors had to flee "
"their country. And so, the art of necromancy was brought to the western "
"continent. While Elyser were wary of humans after the previous invasions, the"
" Necromancers could convince unhappy elves from the lower class to take their"
" chance with magic, which ultimately resulted in the creatiion of darkelves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bowman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"For the longest time Aquana only use spears and swords in melee and javelins "
"for ranged attacks. As they conquered more and more lands they discovered the"
" limit of those weapons in encounters against the Elysian archers. While the "
"conservative leaders clinged to the old ways, more liberal-minded Aquanas "
"chose to replace their javelins with bows. It took a long time, but "
"eventually bows were adapted as the main ranged weapon for its superior range"
" and capacity."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=human
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bowman.cfg:41
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_atlantis.cfg:42
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_long.cfg:41
msgid "bow_variation^Human"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Master_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_atlantis.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Master Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Master_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_atlantis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"With strong shots and precision the Master Bowmen have proven the superiority"
" of bows as ranged weapons to the Aquanian army. The other races archers may "
"laugh at the capability of the typical Aquana bowmen, but they are soon "
"silenced, when thoe masters show their skill in both ranged and close combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_long.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Longbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\bow_long.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Despite the usefulness of bows this weapon is often neglected by the Aquana. "
"Melee weapons are deemed more honorable and only the strongest bowmen can "
"aquire the same admiration as a swords- or spearman. Therefore Aquana bowmen "
"are often trained in sword fighting too and can match many soldiers in melee "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fisherman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisherman.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Fisherman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fisherman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisherman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Fishermen are trained with the use of spear and net, but don't tend to be on "
"the battlefield, if they are not payed well."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=human
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisherman.cfg:61
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_harpuneer.cfg:103
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_retiarius.cfg:66
msgid "fisher_variation^Human"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Harpuuneer, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_harpuneer.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Harpuuneer"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_defense_water
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_harpuneer.cfg:22
msgid "better swimmer (+10% water defense)"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Harpuuneer, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_harpuneer.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Instead of a net, the harpuuneers catch their prey with precicely thrown "
"harpuunes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_harpuneer.cfg:55
msgid "harpuun"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Retiarius, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_retiarius.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Retiarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Retiarius, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\fisher_retiarius.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Veterans of war might pursue a more profitable profession than simple "
"Fishermen. As Gladiators they can gain lots of prestige to climb the social "
"ladder."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Mage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage.cfg:4
msgid "Aquamancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Mage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Legend has it, the mermaids of the sea are the creators of all waves. While "
"this might be an exaggeration, they certanly are the most capable watermages."
" Aquana Mages are direct descendants of those mermaids, which shows in their "
"affinity for water magic."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage.cfg:46
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_blue.cfg:64
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Fullmoon.cfg:65
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Newmoon.cfg:61
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Enchantress.cfg:56
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Initiate.cfg:56
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Siren.cfg:62
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Motbe.cfg:67
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s1-Gnome_rider.cfg:39
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s2-Gnome_knight.cfg:43
msgid "iceball"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage.cfg:97
msgid "female^Aquamancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Blue_Mage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_blue.cfg:4
msgid "Blue Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Blue_Mage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_blue.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The blue Mages of Atlantis have spend much time on and under water. Their "
"study of mermaids and knowledge of the ocean really shows when they cast huge"
" waves and powerful streams of water."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_blue.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Blue Mages have a higher resistance to ‘fire’ "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_blue.cfg:114
msgid "female^Blue Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fullmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Fullmoon.cfg:4
msgid "Fullmoon Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fullmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Fullmoon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"To be accepted in the circle of Fullmoon Mages the Blue Mages have to undergo"
" countless rituals. They spend months alone on the sea, countering the forces"
" of nature with their own magic. This procedure starts and ends on a full "
"moon.\n"
"Each Mage dyes their hair in a silver colour, to show their status. They "
"wield a trident and a silver orb, symbols of water and moon. The mightiest "
"Mage can aquire the title 'Mage of the blue Element' and rules over the city "
"of Atlantis."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Fullmoon.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Fullmoon Mages have a higher resistance to ‘fire’ "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Fullmoon.cfg:116
msgid "female^Fullmoon Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Newmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Newmoon.cfg:4
msgid "Newmoon Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Newmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Newmoon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Newmoon Mages are often blamed for all the bad things happening to the "
"Aquanas. They dress in dark Robes and distance themself from society. But in "
"reality the Mages are no more evil than any other person. The dark Robes "
"ressemble a moonless night and they only distance themself to study in peace."
" Newmoon Mages belong to a proud circle. They are often stronger than their "
"counterpart, because they focus on water and ice magic instead of healing and"
" politics."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Newmoon.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Newmoon Mages have a higher resistance to ‘fire’ "
"and 'cold' attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\mage_Newmoon.cfg:112
msgid "female^Newmoon Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Mercenary, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Mercenary"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Mercenary, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The spear is the traditional weapon of the Aquana. It is cheap in production "
"and can be used under water more effectively than most other weapons. Over "
"time the Aquana have developed different styles for the spearhead. Commonly "
"used is a a large one with a sharpened edge which can be used for piercing "
"and slashing alike.Long peaceful timeperiods have made it unnecessary for the"
" Aquana to have a standing army. Now most soldiers are untrained peasants and"
" mercenaries."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=human
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc.cfg:58
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_general.cfg:72
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_guard.cfg:62
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_hoplite.cfg:70
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_tank.cfg:51
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_warrior.cfg:39
msgid "merc_variation^Human"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_General, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_general.cfg:4
msgid "Atlantis General"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_General, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_general.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Most of  Atlantis' Generals come from rich families. They were trained in the"
" arts of combat and war from young age and are now as capable as leaders as "
"they are with the sword. Normal Soldiers can only aquire this rank through "
"hard work in many won battles."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_general.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Generals have a higher resistance to ‘impact’ and "
"'blade' attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_general.cfg:48
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Hoplite.cfg:54
#: .\units\RE_units\marashy\w1-Soldier.cfg:37
#: .\units\RE_units\marashy\w2-Longsword.cfg:38
#: .\units\RE_units\marashy\w3-Swordmaster.cfg:40
msgid "shield"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Guard, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_guard.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Spearguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Guard, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_guard.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Like the common Aquana spearman the spearguards have special pikes, that "
"allow them to slash and pierce. In great numbers they can easily subdue enemy"
" cavalry and act as protection to archers and mages."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_guard.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Spearguards have a higher resistance to ‘pierce’ "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Hoplite, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_hoplite.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Hoplite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Hoplite, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_hoplite.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Strong and tall stand the Aquana Hoplites in battle. Their defense can hardly"
" be broken, even by fearsome foes, while the long pikes pose a threat to "
"anyone stupid enough to engage them in melee."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_hoplite.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Hoplits have higher resistances to every type "
"except fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Tank, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_tank.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Heavy Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Tank, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_tank.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Heavily armored and equipped with greatswords the elite of Aquanian swordsmen"
" can face anyone in close combat. What they lack in speed they make up for "
"with pure strenght and resiliance."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_tank.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Heavy Swordsmen wear thick armor, which offers additinal protection in trade "
"of movement and evasion."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_tank.cfg:41
msgid "Bastard sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warrior_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warrior_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_warrior.cfg:20
msgid ""
"All Aquana soldiers start as mercenary. They use cheap weapons, like spears, "
"because they are easier to handle and more efficient in large numbers. If a "
"warrior proves himself he can switch his choice of weapon. While swordsmen "
"might not be as powerful on the battlefield, the strength and speed of their "
"weapon exceeds in duels."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\merc_warrior.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Compared to other Aquana, Spearguards have a higher resistance to ‘impact’ "
"and 'blade' attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Enchantress, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Enchantress.cfg:4
msgid "female^Aquana Mermaid Enchantress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Enchantress, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Enchantress.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Mermaids, like elves, have a powerful and native ability in magic, though "
"theirs is considerably different than that of the elves. Those who master "
"this ability are held in high regard, and their skill is used in a multitude "
"of crafts, many of which humanity would never dream. The obvious use in war "
"is forbidden against their own race — this power is the greater part of what "
"protects their people from the monsters that wander out of the abyss."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fighter, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Fighter, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Fighter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Skilled denizens of the sea, Mermen are powerful and quick in any watery "
"environment, but lose most of their mobility on land."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warden, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Hoplite.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Warden"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warden, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Hoplite.cfg:20
msgid ""
"With their towering shields, the Merman Wardens form the elite guard of the "
"watery realm. Their powerful armor and rigid discipline allow them to hold a "
"steadfast line in the maelstrom of battle. In times of desperation, they can "
"even do so on land, though not nearly as well as a creature with legs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Hunter, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Hunter.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Hunter, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Hunter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The skills employed by mermen in spear-fishing are easily translated into "
"warfare, especially against those who are not at home in the water. In times "
"of need, many mermen of that occupation will volunteer to swell the ranks of "
"their military."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Initiate, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Initiate.cfg:4
msgid "female^Aquana Mermaid Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Initiate, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Initiate.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Young mermaids are often initiated into the water magics native to their "
"people. The wondrous abilities this grants are inimitable by any other race, "
"a mark of the faerie side of these creatures.Despite their frailty, this "
"makes them quite formidable in combat, as they can call upon the very water "
"about them to smite their enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Javelineer, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Javelineer.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Javelineer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Javelineer, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Javelineer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Those mermen who master the art of the javelin can become nearly as effective"
" as an archer — though the heft of their weapons impedes their range, the "
"impact of one is considerably greater. In the water, the mobility of the "
"mermen more than makes up for this when facing foes who cannot swim."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Entangler, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Netcaster.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Netcaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Entangler, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Netcaster.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Fishing, as practiced by mermen, is largely a matter of chasing schools of "
"fish into waiting nets, where oar-like clubs are used to dispatch the prey. "
"The improvisation of using these against soldiers proved very effective; most"
" land-native creatures are already quite awkward when waist-deep in water, "
"and getting caught in a net can render them nearly helpless.The effectiveness"
" of this method led to the development of smaller, weighted nets, which could"
" be cast through the air; these were useless for fishing, but were useful in "
"both combat, and in hunting game that came too close to shore. Clubs were "
"used in combat with little or no adaptation from fishing, since they were "
"already quite deadly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Siren, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Siren.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Mermaid Siren"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Siren, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Siren.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The faerie nature of the mermaids is strongest in the Sirens, whose "
"connection to the currents of magic often causes them to be mistaken for "
"naiads themselves. Though certainly far from the truth, the mistake is "
"understandable, as true naiads are rarely seen even by mermaids. The "
"manifestation of their magic is certainly very similar; the water about a "
"siren can be commanded at whim, like an extension of herself.The myriad "
"applications of this rarely occur to land dwellers, who simply regard it with"
" wonder."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Siren.cfg:38
msgid "naia touch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Spearman, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Spearman.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Spearman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Spearman, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Spearman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Archery is little favored by the mermen, for whom use of javelins serves a "
"similar function. Though thrown javelins are of little use under the water, "
"they are extremely effective at the surface, where their weight allows them "
"to plunge several feet below the water while retaining enough momentum to "
"wreak damage. They are also useful in melee, even deep under the surface, "
"which is something that certainly cannot be said of arrows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Triton, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Triton.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Triton"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Triton, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Triton.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Tritons are combat masters of the sea. Skilled in use of the trident, Tritons"
" easily defeat any enemy foolish enough to wander into their preferred "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warrior_Merman, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Merman Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Warrior_Merman, race=merman
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Merman_Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Mermen Warriors form the core of the mermen armies. Wielding powerful "
"tridents, they are a bane to any who dare enter their waters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_High_Fullmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Motbe.cfg:4
msgid "Mage of the blue element"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_High_Fullmoonmage, race=AE_RHY_aquana, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\Motbe.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Fullmoon mage Fiora is currently the strongest Aquana Mage and ruler of "
"Atlantis. Her control over water is legendary and she is admired by her "
"citizens."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Scout, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Mercenary Scout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Scout, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The mercenary Scouts are the basic cavalry of the Aquana. In peaceful times "
"they protect caravans from bandits. The Scouts often unite under more "
"experienced mercenaries in hope of new assignments.A rumors says some of them"
" hire bandits to attack merchants, who refuse to pay the mercenaries for "
"protection."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout.cfg:19
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_knight.cfg:20
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_rider.cfg:20
msgid "The human variation trades some cold resistance for arcane resistance."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=human
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout.cfg:63
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_knight.cfg:77
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_rider.cfg:84
msgid "rider_variation^Human"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Knight, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_knight.cfg:4
msgid "Atlantis Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Knight, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_knight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The elite cavalry of Atlantis is capable of defending itself in water, though"
" their prefered terrain is still on land. They are often in charge of a group"
" of mercinaries, because their fame and strenght attracts wealthier customers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Rider, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_rider.cfg:4
msgid "Aquana Mercenary Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_aq_Rider, race=AE_RHY_aquana
#: .\units\RE_units\aquana\scout_rider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Mercenary Riders are veterans of battle and have earned the respect of other "
"warriors. Therefore they are often in charge of other soldiers and they "
"manage assignments given by the merchants. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Ballista, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\ballista.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Ballista"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Ballista, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\ballista.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A ballista is a warmachine which can shoot arrows over a large distance. It "
"is able to shoot at he enemy, while staying out of the range of archers, but "
"it has no use in melee. The operator of this machinery is a trained engineer "
"and can repair broken parts.Note: Shoot by selecting ballista, then right "
"click on enemy in range 2 (one field between unit and enemy) and use 'Fire "
"Arrow'. Can not shoot while enemy unit is next to ballista."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\ballista.cfg:57
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\scorpio.cfg:56
msgid "longshot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Bartender, race=AE_RHY_dwarf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\barkeep.cfg:4
msgid "Bartender"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Bartender, race=AE_RHY_dwarf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\barkeep.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Barkeeps distribute the most important resource, the ale. Without this drink "
"dwarvish society could not function and their soldiers would not be half as "
"scary.\n"
"\t\n"
"The dwarvish Bartenders know how to handle unpleasant customers. Be it with "
"their fist or with a crossbow hidden behind the counter."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\barkeep.cfg:40
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\brewmaster.cfg:42
msgid "Toss Ale"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Brewmaster, race=AE_RHY_dwarf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\brewmaster.cfg:4
msgid "Brewmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Brewmaster, race=AE_RHY_dwarf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\brewmaster.cfg:22
msgid ""
"One of the most respectable professions in dwarvish society - maybe aside "
"from the king- is the brewmaster.\n"
"Brewmasters extended knowledge of all sorts of herbs have given them the "
"ability to unpoison. Does not work on headaches."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Engineer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Engineer.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Engineer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Engineer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Engineer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Dwarvish engineers construct mining-golems and warmachines. They are often "
"seen improving the mechanism on their crossbow for more powerful shots."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_War_Engineer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Engineer_war.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish War Engineer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_War_Engineer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Engineer_war.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Rather than operating a war machine, these engineers are responsible for its "
"maintenance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardknight, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardknight.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Lizardknight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardknight, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardknight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Dwarvish Lizardknights prefer a breed of lizards with hard plates on their "
"head, so they can charge into battle without having to worry about the safety"
" of their mount."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardknight.cfg:30
msgid "headbutt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardrider, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardrider.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Lizardrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardrider, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardrider.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Horned Lizards are harder to tame due to being more agressive, but the "
"stubborness of dwarves can make even these mighty beasts submit."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardscout, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardscout.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Lizardscout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lizardscout, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lizardscout.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The massive lizards are the perfect mounts for the short legged dwarves to "
"explore terrain outside of their mountains."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Miner, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Miner.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Miner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Miner, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Miner.cfg:17
msgid "In dwarvish culture, even Miners are allowed to drink."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Miner.cfg:34
msgid "Pick axe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runeknight, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\runeknight.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Runeknight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runeknight, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\runeknight.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The armor and weapons of Runeknights have arcane runes carves in by masterful"
" Runesmiths. They protect the warrior from magical influence and can "
"magicallly guide and strengthen their attacks.\n"
"Due to the expensiveness of Runecraft, this equipment is very rare."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\runeknight.cfg:54
msgid "lightning blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runemage, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage.cfg:4
msgid "Runemage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runemage, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage.cfg:22
msgid ""
"It takes a long time of study to master runemagic, but with this power "
"dwarvish mages can fight on equal footing with sorcerers of other races. "
"Runemages are often lighter equipped as other dwarves, but their robes give a"
" good protection against the elements, especially fire, and they wear "
"chainmail underneath as protection against physical attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage.cfg:36
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Adept.cfg:35
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Elementarist.cfg:39
msgid "rune of fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runeadept, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Adept.cfg:4
msgid "Runeadept"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Runeadept, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Adept.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Unlike gnomes,elves and fairies, dwarves have no noteworthy connection to the"
" spirit of living things, rendering them unable to use most kinds of magic. "
"Through intense research of magic capabilities of ore and stone they stumbled"
" upon a different kind of sorcery. By creating powerful runes Runemages and "
"their adepts can use the power of earth itself to summon magical fireballs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Elementarist, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Elementarist.cfg:4
msgid "Elementarist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Elementarist, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Elementarist.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The strongest and wisest of the Runemages are given the title Elementarist. "
"With the power of runes they can control fire and ice with ease."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Runemage_Elementarist.cfg:51
msgid "rune of ice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Scorpio, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\scorpio.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Scorpio"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Scorpio, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\scorpio.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A scorpio is a warmachine which can shoot arrows over a large distance. It is"
" able to shoot at he enemy, while staying out of the range of archers, but it"
" has no use in melee. The operator of this machinery is a trained engineer "
"and can repair broken parts.Note: Shoot by selecting the scorpio, then right "
"click on enemy in range 2 (one field between unit and enemy) and use 'Fire "
"Arrow'. Can not shoot while enemy unit is next to scorpio."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\scorpio.cfg:47
msgid "scorpio"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Archer, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\a1-Archer_Dark.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Archer, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\a1-Archer_Dark.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Since bows are less useful in caves and deep forests, the home of the "
"darkelves, the dark archers are less trained in ranged combat than other "
"elven bowmen. The rough enviroment has made them stronger and more resilient "
"though."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\a2-Archer_Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\a2-Archer_Shadow.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Shadowarchers are used to dark enviroments and well trained with the bow."
" They use their enhanced vision to strike when their enemy is almost blind "
"and can't even see the blackened arrows coming."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nighteye, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\a3-Archer_Nighteye.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The elite darkelven archers are named after their remarkable ability to see "
"in the darkest places and shoot their victims with great accuracy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Queen, race=AE_RHY_undead, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Dark_Queen.cfg:4
msgid "Darkelven Queen"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Queen, race=AE_RHY_undead, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Dark_Queen.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Meloen, heir of house Li'ath and queen of the dark elves, has led her folk "
"for many centuries. Her elvish blood bleesed her with a long lifespan, but "
"through necromancy she achieved immortality.She is one of the oldest and most"
" powerful Liches in existence. Her presence alone makes lawful units tremble "
"in fear, while her own soldiers fight with unnatural strenght. Her own "
"physical capabilities are hardly noteworthy, but she posseses almost "
"unmatched magic capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Thief, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e1-Thief.cfg:4
msgid "Darkelf Thief"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Thief, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e1-Thief.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The thief guild is highly valued by darkelves. The thiefs are often hired to "
"infiltrate cities, cause chaos and gather informations. They carry small "
"knives and a crossbow, which can shoot grappling irons to quickly climb "
"walls."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightshadow, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e2-Nightshadow.cfg:4
msgid "Nightshadow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightshadow, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e2-Nightshadow.cfg:17
msgid ""
"With their ability to sneak almost without any sound through the night the "
"darkelven Nightshadows are capable Assassins. They act in sets of two, where "
"one distracts the enemy while the other one strikes him down."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Assassin, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e3-Assassin.cfg:4
msgid "Darkelf Assassin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Assassin, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e3-Assassin.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The darkelven thief guild trains the most capable assassins in the world. "
"They can move silently through the night and easily slip through enemy ranks."
" Their crossbows are equipped with poisioned dart to kill even the toughest "
"target. Additionally they have learned how to kill someone with a single "
"strike, though this is difficult to execute and only possible when the victim"
" is distracted."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:5
msgid "Assassin Grandmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:19
msgid "become a better swordfighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:30
msgid "slow your enemy with your daggers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:44
msgid "Hide in Forest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:56
msgid "Hide in Villages"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:68
msgid "become a better Assassin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:79
msgid "Learn how to use a bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_GreatassassinB, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:134
msgid ""
"Assassin Grandmasters have trained their whole live to become the perfect "
"killers. They know how to hide and sneak and most importantly, how to kill. "
"The Grandmasters can use poison to weaken and swords to kill, but the most "
"remarkable ability is to murder the target with a single strike from the "
"shadows."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Greatassassin-AMLA.cfg:136
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Masterassassin.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The deathstrike only uses 4 movement, so the Assasin can still get away after"
" attacking this way."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Greatassassin, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Masterassassin.cfg:4
msgid "Master Assassin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Greatassassin, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\e4-Masterassassin.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Master Assassins have truely earned their title. They are as evasive as they "
"are deadly. Beside crossbow and dagger they have also trained with sword, to "
"defend themself in dire situations."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spearman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f1-Spearman.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Spearman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spearman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f1-Spearman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The common darkelven infantryman joins the dark legion. Equipped with long "
"spears and a few light javelins the spearmen can hold the ground against "
"enemy cavalry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkguard, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f2-Darkguard.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkguard, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f2-Darkguard.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The dark guard consists of veteran darkelven spearmen. The elven guards are "
"often weaker than their human counterpart in melee, but they carry around "
"small javelins for ranged combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowwarrior, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f2-Shadowwarrior.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowwarrior, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f2-Shadowwarrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Aside from the Dark Guard and the Shadowarchers, the Warrior guild is the "
"most common guild for any experienced darkelven footsoldier. Instead of "
"spears, like the Dark Guard, the Shadow Warriors train with swords and bows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowguard, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f3-Crescent.cfg:4
msgid "Crescent Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowguard, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f3-Crescent.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Crescent Warriors are the private guard of the darkelven queen. The "
"namegiving spearhead on their weapon is formed like a crescent moon and can "
"be used to hook, slash or pierce an enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f3-Crescent.cfg:38
msgid "Mooncleave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowgeneral, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f3-Shadowgeneral.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow General"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowgeneral, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\f3-Shadowgeneral.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Older darkelven soldiers have aquired much experience in battle and can get "
"anointed general by the queen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowprincess, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\l2-Shadowprincess.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow Princess"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowprincess, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\l2-Shadowprincess.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The descendants of the noble house of Li'ath were one of the few elvish "
"aristrocrats who were tempted by the dark magic. Their noble bloodline gives "
"them respect among others, so they often act as leaders to the darkelves. As "
"members of the upper class the princesses have access to the best training in"
" magic and combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightprincess, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\l3-Nightprincess.cfg:4
msgid "Princess of the Night"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightprincess, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\l3-Nightprincess.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Meloen, heir of house Li'ath and queen of the dark elves, has led the "
"darkelves for many centuries. Her elvish blood bleesed her with a long "
"lifespan, but through necromancy she achieved immortality. Only she can "
"choose who wears the title of Princess and only few have aquired this honor. "
"The Princess of the night is capable in magic and sword and has shown a "
"tactical finesse. As a powerful dark mage she can emitt a shadow aura."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m1-Priest_Dark.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Priest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m1-Priest_Dark.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Like most species, Elves despise dark magic and exile or kill anyone who "
"practices the dark arts. The exiled Mages have joined with other outlaw Elves"
" and found a new home in caves and dark forests, that even Wood Elves avoid. "
"The Dark Elven Priests experiment with poison, necromacy, bloodmagic and "
"summoning. Some have even developed an immunity against venom and poisons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow Priest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Shadow.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Black Magic influences elves in a different way than most other races. Their "
"fairy nature is corupted by the dark arts and their mind and bodies begin to "
"change. The warm aura, which some elves have, gets cold and black enough to "
"turn the surroundings into darkness."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Shadow.cfg:26
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Blood.cfg:28
msgid "hookstaff"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spiderpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Spider.cfg:4
msgid "Spider Priest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spiderpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Spider.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Spider Priests are masterful defilers. They produce the weapons of the "
"Darkelf Assassins and are responsible for raising the domesticated spiders. "
"The Priests have studied and dissected many cave spiders to improve their "
"magic with poisoning and slowing attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Spider.cfg:27
msgid "spider staff"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Spider.cfg:40
msgid "poison curse"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m2-Priest_Spider.cfg:52
msgid "magical web"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Bloodpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Blood.cfg:4
msgid "Bloodpriest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Bloodpriest, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Blood.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Darkelven Bloodpriests have specialiced in the dark art of Bloodmagic. They "
"can cast powerful spells at cost of their lifeforce, but it's mostly their "
"ability to cover their surrounding in darkness that makes them valuable "
"members in the dark army."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Blood.cfg:50
msgid "bloodburn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Summoner, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Summoner.cfg:4
msgid "Darkelf Summoner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Summoner, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Summoner.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Akuma-Edryal, a Darkelf Necromancer, was the first in aeons to summon a demon"
" into this world. While researching how to create more powerful undeads he "
"stumbled on a book in an abandoned Rashky library. He could only roughly "
"translate the contents, so he did not understand what he summoned, nor how he"
" could control the beast. The Demon killed the master and most of his "
"students, but Elacyn, a young Adept, managed to banish the fiend again with "
"another spell from the book.\n"
"Elacyn continued to study the contents of the library and became known as the"
" first true Darkelf Summoner. He took many students and created a demon army "
"to conquer the world, but it ultimately failed when the demons found a way to"
" break their chains and turned against their masters.The other races "
"destroyed the Demons and drove the Darkelves back, but the Summoner caste is "
"still an important part in darkelven culture.A Summoner can cast unworldly "
"magic and summon lesser demons, but the first spell they have to learn is "
"always a banishment hex."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Summoner.cfg:32
msgid "cursed dagger"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\m3-Priest_Summoner.cfg:44
msgid "chaos wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Maceman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\maceman.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Maceman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Maceman, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\maceman.cfg:22
msgid ""
"These soldiers however often act as bodyguards for important members of the "
"darkelves society. As such, they forgo the typical light armor of elves for a"
" heavier variant. The elven nibleness still lets then defend reasonably well "
"in most terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\maceman.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Compared to other Elves, Maceman have a higher resistance, but less defense "
"on difficult terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Trooper, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\mace_trooper.cfg:4
msgid "Black Trooper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Trooper, race=AE_RHY_darkelf, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\mace_trooper.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The Black troopers are intimidating forces on the battlefield. The cage at "
"the end of their flail is filled with hot burning coals, which can set fire "
"to the target."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\mace_trooper.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Compared to other Elves, Troopers have a higher resistance, but less defense "
"on difficult terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\mace_trooper.cfg:58
msgid "flail fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s1-Rider_Dark.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Darkrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s1-Rider_Dark.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Darkelves do not have a large number of cavalerists, but even a small group "
"of horsemen is capable of pillaging and burning down villages."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s2-Rider_Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Shadowrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s2-Rider_Shadow.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Shadow Riders are capable horsemen in melee, though they prefer a hit and"
" run tactic due to their fast movement and exellent bowmanship."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s3-Rider_Night.cfg:4
msgid "Moon Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Nightrider, race=AE_RHY_darkelf
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\s3-Rider_Night.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Night Riders set out in small groups to wreak havoc in undefended "
"villages. Their terrifying apperance, when they show up in the night to burn "
"down cities, has given them the nickname Night-mares."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Small_Spider, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spider.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Spider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Small_Spider, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The big black spiders live in caves and in the forest. Though human-sized "
"creatures are not normally their prey, their bites can inflict deadly poison "
"and should not be underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spiderling, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spiderling.cfg:4
msgid "Spiderling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Spiderling, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spiderling.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Spiderlings don't pose a big threat on their own, but they can hatch in huge "
"numbers, swarming the enemy and killing them with their poison."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Black_Spider, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spider_Big.cfg:4
msgid "Black Widow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Black_Spider, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\Spider_Big.cfg:21
msgid ""
"One of the deadliest hunters in caves is the enormous black widow. Once you "
"get cought up in her net there is almost no escape from her deadly poison."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Dark_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\t1-wose_dark.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Dark_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\t1-wose_dark.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Dark Woses were corrupted through black magic. The Mages have tormented the "
"mostly peaceful creatures to a point where they want to take revenge on every"
" living being. Dark Woses are better adapted to the harsh enviroment -like "
"caves- , where darkelves live in, and are more resistant against the cold. "
"The torture has permanetly damaged their wood-like body,  making them weaker "
"against blade and impact weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Deadwood, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\t2-wose_dead.cfg:4
msgid "Deadwood"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_de_Deadwood, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elves-dark\t2-wose_dead.cfg:28
msgid ""
"While far from dead, the Deadwoods got the name from their resemblance to "
"rotten trees. They usually get nutrients from the ground, but Deadwoods can "
"also directly feed on corpses.\n"
"\n"
"As they grow, their bark can turn even harder."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Archer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a1-Archer.cfg:4
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a1-Archer.cfg:54
msgid "Elyser Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Archer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a1-Archer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Elves have always had a reputation for archery, a skill that, for many "
"reasons, comes naturally to them. Even the frail of body can be deadly with a"
" bow in hand, and in times of war, many will take up this weapon. Though "
"their relative inexperience with combat leaves them somewhat vulnerable, "
"their natural grace ensures that they can best any of humanity’s fresh "
"recruits."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a2-Marksman.cfg:4
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a2-Marksman.cfg:77
msgid "Elyser Longbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a2-Marksman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Elves are wonderously keen-sighted, a gift which contributes to their mastery"
" of the bow. An elf practiced at archery can hit targets that a man couldn’t "
"even see, and can nock a second arrow almost as soon as the first is let fly."
" Realizing this prodigious skill does come with one cost, that being a lack "
"of practice with the sword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sharpshooter, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a3-Sharpshooter.cfg:4
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a3-Sharpshooter.cfg:80
msgid "Elyser Sharpshooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sharpshooter, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\a3-Sharpshooter.cfg:21
msgid ""
"here was a legend of an elf who stopped an arrow by shooting it out of the "
"air with one of his own. It is a testament to the skill of the elves that "
"such a story could be taken seriously. The sharpshooters of the elves have, "
"quite simply, mastered the art of archery."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f1-Fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f1-Fighter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Elves are not warlike by nature, but in times of need, their natural grace "
"and agility serve them well, as does their skillful craftsmanship. An elf can"
" grasp the basics of swordsmanship and archery in a time uncannily short by "
"the standards of other races, and put them to effective use on the "
"battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Champion, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f3-Champion.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Champion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Champion, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f3-Champion.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Those few elves who deliberately hone themselves into weapons of war become "
"something which belies the peace-loving reputation of their race. Dedication "
"and skill are matched with purity of form, and the result is swordsmanship to"
" which few can compare. Even their archery, treated as a secondary pursuit, "
"is masterfully executed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Dancer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f3-Dancer.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Sworddancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Dancer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\f3-Dancer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Elves, though not warlike by nature, are swift to learn; a relatively small "
"amount of experience will turn an elf from a competent fighter into a master "
"of combat. Sworddancers move gracefully through the battlefield while cutting"
" down any obstacle in their path with swift motions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Governor, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Governor.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Governor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Governor, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Governor.cfg:19
msgid ""
"High Lord Gymyr has been governor of Elysys for almost a century and led his "
"citizens in troubled times. In his long lifespan he became a master "
"swordsman, capable sorcerer and respected tactician."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_High_Lord, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\High_Lord.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser High Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_High_Lord, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\High_Lord.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The leaders of elvenkind command an instinctive loyalty from their people "
"that rulers of other races can only envy, and earn it with great mindfulness "
"and wisdom. Quiet and contemplative in times of peace, a High Lord in the "
"full of his wrath is an awesome sight indeed.Unlike wood-elves the Elyser do "
"have an aristroctratic upper class consisting of many noble houses. The "
"highest ranking lords form the Elysian council, led by the governor. As the "
"highest institution, the council is unregulated, which often leads to "
"discontent in the lower classes."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\High_Lord.cfg:75
msgid "female^High Lady"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Noble, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l1-Noble.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Noble"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Noble, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l1-Noble.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Young Elysian nobles have not truely earned their place in society yet, but "
"inherited it form their parents. They posses strong affinity to fairy magic, "
"but are also trained in basic fightingskills and politics."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l1-Noble.cfg:68
msgid "female^Noble"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sorcerer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l3-Sorceress.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Sorcerer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sorcerer, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l3-Sorceress.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Elyser Nobles, who have a strong affinity to magic or no interest in "
"politics, often forego their title to study sorcery. Many other nobles look "
"down on them, but their strength and wisdom is respected by the smallfolk."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\l3-Sorceress.cfg:69
msgid "female^Sorceress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Lord, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Lord.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Lord, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Lord.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The nobility of the ELF are possessed of merit to match their standing in "
"society. Elvish Lords are the wisest and strongest of their people, and are "
"fearsome in their command of magic."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Lord.cfg:72
msgid "female^Lady"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Shaman, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m1-Shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Shaman, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m1-Shaman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Being partly faerie in nature, elves have an inherent capability for magic. "
"This is realized in their affinity with the natural world, which they can "
"call upon as an ally in combat. Enemies wandering in their forests may soon "
"find themselves entangled by roots and hindered by the very ground they stand"
" on.The healing abilities of the elves are also remarkable, and of capital "
"use in battle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Healer, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m2-Healer.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Healer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Healer, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m2-Healer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Nature magic is poorly suited for combat, but effective nonetheless. The "
"forests can become quickened by a word of command, and will lash out at those"
" who threaten the peace.Elysian Healers take care of the sick. Their magic "
"can close wounds quickly and their knowledge of nature and healing herbs "
"helps them treat any illness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Druid, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m3-Druid.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Druid, race=AE_RHY_elyser, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\m3-Druid.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Elisian Druids have a deep connection to the forest and nature itself. They "
"can command it at will to subdue any threat.The chief ability of Druids lies "
"in healing, and it is for this skill that they are revered by their people. "
"Though less effective, they can also use magic to heal themself."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Scout, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s1-Scout.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Scout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Scout, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s1-Scout.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The horsemen of the wood elves have some skill with bow and sword, but their "
"true skill lies in their horsemanship. Even other elves are impressed by "
"their uncanny speed in the woods, and their ability to dart through the thick"
" of the forest with nary a scratch. They may be the only cavalry in existence"
" that fares better in the woods than on open ground."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Rider, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s2-Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Rider, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s2-Rider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The master horsemen of the elves are able to move through forests at a speed "
"which would be suicidal for any human. Awe of the rider is quite justified — "
"but questions have also been raised about the stock of the horses, for the "
"feats they perform seem almost supernatural.This combination of incredible "
"mobility and potent combat strength is one of the greatest assets the elves "
"possess in warfare."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Outrider, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s3-Outrider.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Avantgarde"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Outrider, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\s3-Outrider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Elvish Outriders are trained as the royal couriers of the elven kingdoms. "
"Despite the peaceful nature of their people, their experience makes them "
"quite deadly in combat. No human has ever come close to their skill in using "
"a bow on horseback — in fact, most would be hard pressed to equal it standing"
" on solid ground.The speed of these soldiers allows the elves to strike when "
"and where they choose when fighting on their home ground, a fact that has "
"saved many of their number from death."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sylph, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Sylph.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Sylph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sylph, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Sylph.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Sylph is an honorary title for the most powerful sorcerers in Elysys, as no "
"Elyser reached the power of a true Sylph for a long time. Elysian Sylphs have"
" hardly any control over nature, like their wood-elven counterpart, but the "
"strength of their fairy magic in not to be underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Sylph.cfg:72
msgid "female^Sylph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Guard, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\t2-Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Guard, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\t2-Guard.cfg:22
msgid ""
"To protect their city the Elysians have estabished the order of guards. Those"
" heavily armored elves can easily defend citywalls or battlelines. The large "
"spear and shield does not allow them to use a bow anymore, but the additional"
" defense is well worth it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\t3-Sentinel.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_elyser
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\t3-Sentinel.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Elysian Sentinels are dangerous opponents. Their -for elven standarts- large "
"shield and heavy armor makes them very resistant against physical weapons and"
" the spears are devestating melee weapons. Despite their size, their spears "
"are surprisingly light, which allows the Sentinels to attack faster than "
"normal spearmen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Waterfairy, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waterfairy.cfg:4
msgid "Water fairy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Waterfairy, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waterfairy.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Over time Pixies gather more magic, which enhances their body aswell as their"
" magical power."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Nymph, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waternymph.cfg:4
msgid "Elyser Nymph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Nymph, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waternymph.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Pixies, who spent a lot of time in water, might grow a fish tail and loose "
"their Wings. They grow far taller than normal Pixies and are often confused "
"with mermaids.A Nymphs singing is so beautiful, it can break the will of all "
"men. The secret behind this is her fairy magic, which she weaves into each "
"tone of her songs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waternymph.cfg:48
msgid "song of the siren"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Waterpixie, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waterpixi.cfg:4
msgid "Water pixie"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Waterpixie, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Waterpixi.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Pixies are small, fragile creatures with a strong connnestion to nature and a"
" resemblance to butterflies. Their apperance and abilities depend on the "
"place of birth -or whatever you would call this process- but can be altered "
"by their lifestyle. Pixies are carefree and therefore often appear as "
"mischievous.\n"
"\t\n"
"Pixies born near water have control over the same. They use it to play tricks"
" on travelers, but, unless angered, they do not harm people with it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Watersylph, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Watersylph.cfg:4
msgid "Water sylph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Watersylph, race=merman, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Watersylph.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The older a pixie gets, the stronger she becomes. The highest form is the "
"sylph, which is not to be confused with a sylph of elven heritage. Though "
"they have the same name and similar strengh there are some differences. "
"Elvish Sylphs control nature and fairy magic and their body has changed by "
"their fairy nature. Sylphs of pixie heritage only posses fairy magic, but can"
" only control nature with it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a1-crossbowman.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Crossbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a1-crossbowman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Because of their small size, dwarves rarely use bows. While some dwarves "
"carry thundersticks or hatches, others use their craftsmanship to construct "
"strong and precise crossbows. They always carry around tools, like a hammer, "
"to repair and enhance their weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Tinkerer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a2-crossbow_tinkerer.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Tinkerer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Tinkerer, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a2-crossbow_tinkerer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Dwarves are known for beeing one of the best inventers in the world. Tinkerer"
" use their knowledge of mechanics to enhance the strength of crossbows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Rapidfire, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a3-crossbow_rapidfire.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Rapidfire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Rapidfire, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a3-crossbow_rapidfire.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some Tinkerers have developed a mechanism that allows to fire crossbows at a "
"great speed. This unfortunately comes at cost of accuracy."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a3-crossbow_rapidfire.cfg:41
msgid "rapidfire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Sniper, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a3-crossbow_sniper.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Sniper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Sniper, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\a3-crossbow_sniper.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Scopes, training and powerful crossbows allow the dwarvish snipers to shoot "
"enemies from a far range with great accuracy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Musican, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b1-musician.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Musican"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Musican, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b1-musician.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Gnomes have a instincual draw to music and their natural magical ability "
"blends into this seamless."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b1-musician.cfg:26
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b2-minstrel.cfg:27
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b3-bard.cfg:27
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e1-scout.cfg:24
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e2-pathfinder.cfg:29
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e3-ranger.cfg:30
msgid "gnomish sword"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane #previously impact, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=arcane #even though the song is fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b1-musician.cfg:35
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b2-minstrel.cfg:36
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b3-bard.cfg:36
msgid "bardish song"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Minstrel, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b2-minstrel.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Minstrel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Minstrel, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b2-minstrel.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Minstrels spread tales and music around to inspire their allies and break "
"their foe."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Bard, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b3-bard.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Bard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Bard, race=AE_RHY_gnome, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\b3-bard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Though bards sing heroic tales of legends past, their own deeds and "
"adventures would be enough to spur the minds of anyone."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Scout, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e1-scout.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Scout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Scout, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e1-scout.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Gnomes are even smaller than dwarves and far more agile. The few not blessed "
"with magic abilites use this to their advantage by slipping through any enemy"
" formation."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e1-scout.cfg:33
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e2-pathfinder.cfg:38
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e3-ranger.cfg:39
msgid "pocket sand"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e1-scout.cfg:47
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e2-pathfinder.cfg:52
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e3-ranger.cfg:53
msgid "slingshot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Pathfinder, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e2-pathfinder.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Pathfinder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Pathfinder, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e2-pathfinder.cfg:16
msgid "The small stature of gnomes is easy to hide in thicket of forests."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e3-ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\e3-ranger.cfg:17
msgid ""
"As masterful scouts and thieves, these gnomes are a true pain for any "
"opposing army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Lumberjack, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f1_axe_lumberjack.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Lumberjack"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Lumberjack, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f1_axe_lumberjack.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most Forestdwarves work as lumberjack. They don't have the experience or "
"equipment of their brothers in the mountains, but constant work has build "
"thier strength enough to compete with their kin. Lumberjacks have better "
"endurance than dwarvish fighters and can therefore travel faster."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Greataxe, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f2-axe_great.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Greataxe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Greataxe, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f2-axe_great.cfg:17
msgid ""
"In times of war the dwarvish lumberjacks use the big axes to cut down enemies"
" insted of trees."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f2-axe_warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f2-axe_warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Battlehardened dwarvish lumberjacks might choose to become a warrior. They "
"equip themselves with a shield and better armor and mow down enemies with "
"sharp axes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Waraxe, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f3-axe_war.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Waraxe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Waraxe, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f3-axe_war.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some dwarves have enough strength to cut down trees with only a few hits. "
"They prefer big, heavy axes, but they also carry around hatchets incase some "
"puny archer wants to try their luck."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Cutter, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f3_axe_cutter.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forest Cutter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Cutter, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\f3_axe_cutter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Dwarvish cutters are the elite of the dwarvish infantry. They carry around "
"big battle axes and and have better armor than other forestdwarves"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Gryphon.cfg:4
msgid "Tamed Gryphon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Gryphon.cfg:19
msgid ""
"These majestic and powerful creatures are masters of the sky. Gryphons are "
"both dangerous and wary of other intelligent creatures, and thus should not "
"be disturbed without a good reason."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gryphon_young, race=gryphon
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Gryphon_young.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Gryphon Chicken"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gryphon_young, race=gryphon
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Gryphon_young.cfg:17
msgid ""
"To tame a Gryphon they need to be trained as soon as they can fly. In only "
"few months they learn how to hunt, how to defend themself and most important,"
" how to distinguish between friend and foe."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Mage, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m1-Gnome.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Mage, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m1-Gnome.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Arcanary is as natural to gnomes as breathing is to most other creatures. "
"While they have to rely on their allies -the dwarves- for protection, the "
"Gnomes can use their connection to the powers of nature to deal huge damage "
"against any threats."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m1-Gnome.cfg:30
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m2-gnome_luck.cfg:33
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Gnomejumper.cfg:37
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Goldgnome.cfg:38
#: .\units\RE_units\marashy\Mage_Battlemage.cfg:54
#: .\units\RE_units\marashy\Mage_Spellblade.cfg:39
msgid "magic missile"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Luck, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m2-gnome_luck.cfg:4
msgid "Lucky Gnome"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Luck, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m2-gnome_luck.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Gnomes are generally lucky creatures, but some specimen reach new levels. "
"Even normal swishes with their staff seem to magically hit their target."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Jumper, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Gnomejumper.cfg:4
msgid "Gnome Jumper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Jumper, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Gnomejumper.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some Gnomes are so in touch with magic, they can ignore space and time and "
"appear wherever they want."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Gold, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Goldgnome.cfg:4
msgid "Gold Gnome"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Gold, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\m3-Goldgnome.cfg:17
msgid ""
"It is said, Goldgnomes could summon gold from air. Unfortunately they don't "
"share it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Rider, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s1-Gnome_rider.cfg:4
msgid "Hare Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Rider, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s1-Gnome_rider.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Some Gnomes are small enough to ride upon Hares. While they don't look like a"
" threat, one should never underestimate gnomemagic or rabbitbites."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Knight, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s2-Gnome_knight.cfg:4
msgid "Hare Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Gnome_Knight, race=AE_RHY_gnome
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\s2-Gnome_knight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Through magical growth some hares reach almost the size of a wolf. They are "
"stronger and more resistant than regular hares while still keeping their "
"agility and speed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Giant, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t1-Giant.cfg:4
msgid "Giant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Giant, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t1-Giant.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Giants usually live in the wild on their own or sometimes in small groups. "
"Smaller creatures try to avoid their path, as Giants are easily angered. In "
"the past mountain-dwarves used to hunt and enslave them, so many wild Giants "
"bear a grudge against them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Coloss, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t2-Giant_coloss.cfg:4
msgid "Colossus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Coloss, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t2-Giant_coloss.cfg:16
msgid ""
"More civilized giants are sometimes recruited by dwarves. With their brute "
"strenght they can throw large rocks at enemies or simply smash them with a "
"club."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t2-Giant_coloss.cfg:37
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t3-Giant_titan.cfg:41
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Titan_King.cfg:42
msgid "toss"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Titan, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t3-Giant_titan.cfg:4
msgid "Titan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Titan, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\t3-Giant_titan.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Even among the Giants, Titans are huge. Their size along with the long shaft "
"of their weapon gives them superior reach in melee, in case they haven't "
"already defeated their oponent with a large thrown boulder."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Titan_King, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Titan_King.cfg:4
msgid "Titan King"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fd_Titan_King, race=AE_RHY_giant
#: .\units\RE_units\gnomes\Titan_King.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Titan King has earned his title by might. He exeeds all other Titans in "
"resiliance and stregth."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Bowmen are the cheapest artillery unit of the chevalier. They are only "
"lightly equipped, making them faster but more vulnerable. Unlike crossbowmen "
"they can be used to cover the opposing army with large number of arrows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman_Long.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Longbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman_Long.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Longbows have greater firepower and range than a normal sized one. To shoot "
"one the bowmen need a lot of streght, so it is unsuited for amateurs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Siege_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman_siege.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Siege Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Siege_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Bowman_siege.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Additionally to normal ammunition, the siege bowman have enflamable arrows. "
"These are less useful against soldiers, but they might start a fire in a "
"besieged town."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Crossbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Crossbows more expensive than shortbows, so only the better off soldiers are "
"equipped with it. They shoot slower, but the additional power behind each "
"bolt makes up for it. Because of the lower movement range required to operate"
" a crossbow, the soldiers can wear more armor."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman.cfg:21
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_heavy.cfg:24
msgid "pickaxe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Arbalist, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_arbalest.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Arbalist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Arbalist, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_arbalest.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The arbalest has an easy loading mechanism, which allows the arbalist to "
"shoot faster. Due to it's prize only elite crossbowmen can afford it."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_arbalest.cfg:24
msgid "war pickaxe"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_arbalest.cfg:33
msgid "arbalest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Heavy_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_heavy.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier heavy Crossbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Heavy_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Crossbowman_heavy.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The heavy crossbows have an immense firepower, but are hard to load and "
"therefor slow. Only experienced crossbowmen might be equipped with it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Doctor, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doctor.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Doctor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Doctor, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doctor.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Doctors are the most capable healers in the human realm. Their knowledge of "
"healing herbs and basic surgery is asked for in peace and times of war, "
"though their service is costly. Doctors can not only treat their patients, "
"but are also capable of performing healing procedures on their own body if "
"needed. Though they don't fight in front line in battle, Doctors know how to "
"defend themselves with poisonous potions, dispeling magic and their staff."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doctor.cfg:40
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Healer.cfg:35
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Quack.cfg:34
msgid "poison"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Healer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Healer.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Healer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Healer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Healer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Through many years of experimenting Quacks start to learn the effects of "
"different types of plants. Their knowledge can now actually be used to heal, "
"though they have also learned to use poisonous substances more effectively."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Quack, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Quack.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Quack"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Quack, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Quack.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Quacks are often seen traveling through the land to offer medicine to "
"people in need, as long as they are willing to pay. With strange herbs, "
"powders and solution they promise a cure for all desease. Their medical "
"knowledge though is limited at best and not a lot of patients survive their "
"procedures.While this might be the reason why they have to flee villages and "
"cities after a short stay, it also gives them an additional income source "
"from a darker business."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Surgeon, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Surgeon.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Surgeon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Surgeon, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Surgeon.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Surgeons forgo their studies in magic and medicine and instead focus directly"
" on 'helping' their patients through surgeries.\n"
"\t\n"
"Patients do not always include willing subjects."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Doc_Surgeon.cfg:45
msgid "Surgeon Knives"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Holy_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Holy_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Holy Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Holy_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_King, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Holy_Knight.cfg:17
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\King.cfg:17
msgid "become a better fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Holy_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Holy_Knight.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Once a high Inquisitor, Kontinus, the holy Knight, has left the Inquisition "
"because he disagreed with their policies. He joined the Teuton knights and "
"quickly rose in ranks due to his exellent swordsman- and leadership. He "
"wields a holy sword, blessed by the pope himself."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=mounted
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Holy_Knight.cfg:101
msgid "hk_variation^mounted"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Horseman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The basic cavalry of the Chevalier is equipped with a long spear and a "
"chainmail. They are charge in large numbers into the enemy lines to break "
"their formation."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_great_knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman_Grand_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Grand Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_great_knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman_Grand_Knight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The grand knights are ledgends. They have fought and won in many battles and "
"joustings and earned their honor. Their heavy lance makes them superior to "
"other cavalry, but they also know how to defend themself with a sword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horseman_Knight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Knights have proven their courage on the battlefield. As reward they are "
"equipped with better armor and a sword, incase they are trapped in a melee."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Heavy_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horse_Chevalier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Chevaliers are masters in fighting from the horseback. The armor -which even "
"the horse is coverd in- protects them while they cut down enemies with their "
"longsword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Armored_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horse_Cuirassier.cfg:4
msgid "Cuirassier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Armored_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horse_Cuirassier.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The simple cuirass armor can be mass produced, saving a lot of costs to equip"
" armor on the horse. Additionally they equip a light crossbow, that can be "
"operated from horseback."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horse_rider.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Horse_rider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Chevalier riders are lighter equipped than the horsemen. Their simple armor "
"has the advantage of being less expensive and easier to move in."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Sergeant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L1_Sergant.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Sergeant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Sergeant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L1_Sergant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Sergeant is a low-ranking officer in the ranks of an army. Though "
"academically trained, he will need some experience in the field before his "
"leadership is sound and acknowledged."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Lieutenant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L2_Lieutenant.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Lieutenant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Lieutenant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L2_Lieutenant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Trained at swords and crossbows, Lieutenants lead small groups of human "
"soldiers, coordinating their attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_General, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L3_General.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier General"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_General, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L3_General.cfg:17
msgid ""
"As the leaders of their armies, Generals are responsible for the protection "
"of large or important areas in the kingdoms to which they have sworn fealty."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Grand_Marshal, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L4_Marshal.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Grand Marshal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Grand_Marshal, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\L4_Marshal.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The rank of Grand Marshal is one of the most esteemed in the armies of "
"humanity, and those who bear its title have survived many trials by fire, "
"proving both their tactical wit and their considerable mettle at personal "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Miliz, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spearman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Miliz"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Miliz, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spearman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"A large part of every chevalier army are the Miliz. They are trained in the "
"usage of spears to counter enemy cavalary and usually carry a small warhammer"
" against armored infantry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Halberdier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Poleaxeman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Halberdier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The big poleaxes are a versatile weapon. They can be used to crush an enemy's"
" head with the hammer or slice them with the sharp edge, while keeping them "
"away with the pointy end."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:39
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:51
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:60
msgid "poleaxe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Basher, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_mace.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Basher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Basher, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_mace.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Bashers are a brutal force on the battlefield. Their flail is hard to defend "
"against and a brutal hit can easily cripple an enemy, making them vulnerable "
"to further attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Pikeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Pikeman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Pikeman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Pikeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Spear_Pikeman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Pikemen have gathered a lot of experience while fighting in line. Their "
"training enables them to defend themself against other, less trained, "
"spearmen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Swordsman.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Swordsman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Veteran Soldiers can rise in the ranks to a true Swordsman. Their heavier "
"armor and training with sword and shield have boosted their physical "
"resistance and attack."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Greatsword, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Greatsword.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Greatsword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Greatsword, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Greatsword.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Some Chevalier Soldiers prefer to fight with a big twohanded sword instead of"
" a smaller sword and shield. This allows them to overwhelm the enemy with "
"superior reach and strenght. Through the greater mass of the sword, the guard"
" can be used as hammer, if the sword is grabbed by the blade."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Greatsword.cfg:40
msgid "murderstrike"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Soldier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Soldier.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Soldier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Soldier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Soldier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Soldiers are better trained Chevalier infantry and are equipped with "
"chainmail, sword and shield. They are resistant against most physical "
"weapons, but less agile in difficult terrain. They show their true potential "
"in open field and when defending castles and villages."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Teuton, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Teuton.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Teuton"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Teuton, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Teuton.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Teutons belong to a small Order of elite Knights, dedicated to protect their "
"ideals in the human realm. They are masters of the sword and have developed "
"many techniques throughout the ages. With a few precise thrusts they can "
"pierce through the weakpoints of their enemy's armor."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Teuton.cfg:37
msgid "halfswording"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Townguard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Townguard.cfg:4
msgid "Chevalier Townguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ce_Townguard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-chevalier\Sword_Townguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Townguards keep peace and order in a city. They are well trained swordsmen, "
"but are less armored than the ones on the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Based on their performance in training the new recruits of the dardo army are"
" split up in assigned to the legion or bowmen. The bowmen have only light "
"armor, as they do not fight in the front line."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Compositbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow2_comp.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Compositbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Compositbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow2_comp.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The compositbow is more precise and has a greater firepower. It is awarded "
"-along with better armor- to bowmen who have served for some years or proven "
"themself in other ways."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow3_long.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Longbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Bow3_long.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The highest ranking dardo bowmen wield longbows and are the deadliest ranged "
"force of the dardo army. The title is only given to the best archers and "
"raises their status during and after their military duty."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\bow_ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Sand Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\bow_ranger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Due to the harsh conditions, the Rangers had to learn how to treat wounds in "
"addition to being masterful archers and terrifying swordsmen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Striker, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\bow_striker.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Striker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Striker, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\bow_striker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Far in the south of the Dardo empire, the terrain turns from steppe to "
"desert. The bowmen in this terrain are trained for survival under the "
"harshest conditions and have learned to treat poisons of the scorpions in the"
" area.\n"
"Their arrows are specifically shaped to cripple prey."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Chariot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Chariot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Chariot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The Dardo use chariots to reinforce their cavalry with bowmen. Shooting from "
"the wagon instead of a horseback increases the stability and still allows "
"quick movement. While the chariots are exellent on large planes, their size "
"makes it difficult to move and maneuver in narrow or rough terrain.Note: "
"Chariots use only 4 movement on attack instead of all. This allows them to "
"disengage after their attack, if they haven't used all movement yet or moved "
"into an enemies zone of control this turn."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot.cfg:22
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot_war.cfg:27
msgid ""
"This unit can attack while moving, making it easy to disengage after combat. "
"However, it does not cancel the effects of zone of control."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_War_Chariot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot_war.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo War Chariot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_War_Chariot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot_war.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Normal chariots are vulnerable to melee combat, since the charioteer has to "
"steer and can't attack in such close range. The improved war chariots are "
"equipped with blades on the wheels which can severely maim enemies while "
"driving past them.Note: Chariots use only 4 movement on attack instead of "
"all. This allows them to disengage after their attack, if they haven't used "
"all movement yet or moved into an enemies zone of control this turn."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\chariot_war.cfg:46
msgid "bladed wheel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Horseman.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Horseman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Horseman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The wide flat terrain of their homeland is excellent for the dardo horsemen. "
"It trains their mounts in speed and endurance, which gives them an advantage "
"against other cavalry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Lancer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Horse_Lancer.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Lancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Lancer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Horse_Lancer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"On the fast horses the lancers can launch devastating assaults on enemy "
"forces and retreat just as quickly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Imperator, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Imperator.cfg:5
msgid "Dardo Imperator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Imperator, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Imperator.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Like all citizens the Dardo Imperator has to serve in the military for some "
"years. Claudus, the current Imperator, had proven himself as swordsman and "
"rider, but really excelled as strategist."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Imperator.cfg:50
msgid "call arrow strike"
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=mounted
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Imperator.cfg:71
msgid "di_variation^mounted"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Mercenary, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Mercenary.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Mercenary"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Mercenary, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Mercenary.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Dardo often hire Mercenaries from their southern provinces as additional "
"force on the battlefield. Mercenaries wear lighter armor, are more agile, but"
" also less disciplined than regular soldiers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Bountyhunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Merc_Bountyhunter.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Bountyhunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Bountyhunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Merc_Bountyhunter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"More renowned sellswords often deny contracts that would put then on the "
"battlefied, since even an experienced fighter can be overwhelmed with "
"numbers. These merceneries have found more profitable and -with thier "
"skillset- less dangerous work. As Bountyhunters they kill criminals and "
"assassinate enemy generals for a few sacks of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Sellsword, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Merc_Sellword.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Sellsword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Sellsword, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Merc_Sellword.cfg:16
msgid ""
"For a large sum of gold sellswords offer their service as bodyguards or "
"soldiers. Like their codex of honor tells them, they stay loyal to their "
"client ... in most cases atleast."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"These wild riders forgo the protection of heavy armor for increased mobility."
" It often becomes a test of courage to go to the battlefield unarmored, but "
"they wear their scars with pride."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Scout, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_equestrian.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Equestrian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Scout, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_equestrian.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The south of the Dardo imperium is famous for its excellent riders. While an "
"veteran horseman is a terror on the battlefield, the young and untrained "
"still have to prove themself and often act as scouts for the army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Cataphract, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_heavy.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Cataphract"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Cataphract, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_heavy.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Rider and horse of the Cataphract are covered in a thick layer of armor. They"
" are slowed down but the additional weigth allows them to trample down "
"anything in their path."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Horse_Lord, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_lord.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Horse Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Horse_Lord, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\rider_lord.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Riders who achieve the rank of Horse Lord are highly admired by the army. "
"They are master swordfighters on horseback and inspire their fellows to great"
" deeds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Slinger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_0.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Slinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Slinger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_0.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Sometimes the Dardo Legion hires slaves to fill thier ranks. For promise of "
"freedom, they risk their lives in the frontlines.\n"
"Unlike the rest of the army, they are not issued equipment. With no combat "
"training and only a armed with a sling, they have to rely on their agility to"
" survive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Flanker, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_1.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Flanker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Flanker, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_1.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Slingers, who through some miracle have survived some battles are granted "
"freedom. Some chose to stay in the army in a more respected position, to earn"
" their living."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Auxilia, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_2.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Auxilia"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Auxilia, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_2.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The last stage before former slaves can reach full citizenship in the Dardo "
"empire. The hard and bloody journey awards them with voting rights, ability "
"to own houses, their own slaves and to have their children be recognized as "
"citizens aswell.\n"
"\n"
"Auxilia carry different ammunition for their slings. Additional to the hard "
"hitting stone and lead projectiles, they fill small bags with sand, which "
"explode on impact and blind the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\slinger_2.cfg:48
msgid "sand bag"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Legion, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spearman.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Legion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Legion, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spearman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Every male Dardo civilian has to join the army when he comes of age. High "
"borns might choose to become riders, but the common folk fights in the "
"legion. They are trained to fight in close formations and use their shield "
"perfectly in defense."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Captain, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\spear_captain.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Captain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Captain, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\spear_captain.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Captains are tactical legends. They are well versed in combat with sword and "
"spear and their presence alone raises the moral of the troops."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Commander, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\spear_commander.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Commander, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\spear_commander.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Commanders have proven themself to be good fighters, who inspire those around"
" them. They are in charge of a small group of soldiers and have no fear of "
"fighting beside them. The training as a part of legion has tought them how to"
" defend against most weapons, raising their resistance against physical "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Hoplite, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spear_Hoplite.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Hoplite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Hoplite, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spear_Hoplite.cfg:16
msgid ""
"When forming a closed line of shields, the hoplites can hardly be overcome by"
" any assaults. Their near perfect defense is aided by deadly stabs of the "
"heavy spears."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Phalanx, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spear_Phalanx.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Phalanx"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Phalanx, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Spear_Phalanx.cfg:17
msgid ""
"As elite hoplites, the phalanx can from inpenetrateable shieldwalls. A direct"
" assault on such a bulwark equals suicide, as the long spears easily subdue "
"anyone in range."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Justicar, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Sword_Justicar.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Justicar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Justicar, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Sword_Justicar.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Justicars are elite swordsmen who act as peacekeepers. Their actions are "
"defined by a strict code of justice and can sometimes conflict with commands "
"of higher-ups."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Praetorian, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Sword_Preatorian.cfg:4
msgid "Dardo Praetorian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dr_Praetorian, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-dardo\Sword_Preatorian.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Praetorians are hired as personal guards or as city watch. In times of war "
"they often build an elite troop under leadership of a captain."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Archer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a1-bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Archer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a1-bowman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The archers of the forestfolk are usually hunters, but can also use their "
"abilities for combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forester, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a2-forester.cfg:4
msgid "Forester"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forester, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a2-forester.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Forester take care of the forest and the animals in it. As counterpart to the"
" trappers, they watch over animal population so it doesn't get too small or "
"too big."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Poacher, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a2-poacher.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Poacher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Poacher, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a2-poacher.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Poachers know how to hunt the critters of the forest. They are the main "
"provider of meat, fur and trophies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Huntsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a3-huntsman.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Huntsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Huntsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a3-huntsman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"As the best hunters in their village, the huntsmen are also the wealthiest "
"-compared to the other forestdwellers- and highly respected. They shoot "
"arrows with extreme precicion that they can best the skill of elven archers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a3-ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\a3-ranger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Rangers have multiple purposes in their village. They take care of the "
"surrounding forest, scout, hunt prey and defend the village against wild "
"animals and other tribes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Ancient_Druid, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Ancient_Druid.cfg:4
msgid "Ancient Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Ancient_Druid, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Ancient_Druid.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Blessed by the spirits of the forest, Votan the ancient druid has lived for "
"many centuries. While he apears as old man, his stregth should not be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Bearver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Bearver.cfg:4
msgid "Bearver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Bearver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Bearver.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The mighty bearver is part of the beaver family, but grows as big and strong "
"as a bear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Beaver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Beaver.cfg:4
msgid "Beaver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Beaver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Beaver.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The smaller creatures are fairly easy to capture, but hard to train for "
"combat. Beavers are often used by forest dwellers to help with daily taskes, "
"like felling trees or delivering messages across water. During fights they "
"swarm the enemy in large numbers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Great_Beaver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Beaver_Great.cfg:4
msgid "Dire Beaver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Great_Beaver, race=AE_RHY_animal
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Beaver_Great.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Exceptionally big Beavers have devestating bites and can knock people off "
"their feet by swinging their tail."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forestking, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_King.cfg:4
msgid "King of the Forest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forestking, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_King.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Elks are often described as the most majestic creature of the forest. Their "
"body is large enough to ride without problems, while still being able to move"
" in the forest. The large horns and strenght make them very dangeous, so only"
" the best tamers know how to befriend and ride them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_King.cfg:36
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Knight.cfg:35
msgid "horns"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Deerknight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Deerknight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Deerknight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Knight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Stags are buffer than their female counterpart, but harder to tame. Only "
"experienced riders can mount them without being immediately kicked off."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Deerrider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Deerrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Deerrider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Rider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Female deers are shy and hard to capture, but less agressive than the males. "
"Once they are used to humans they can be breeded and trained for riding. "
"Though their are more fragile than horses, the deers are nimble enough to "
"move unhindered in the forest."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Deer_Rider.cfg:35
msgid "hooves"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Hunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f1_hunter.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Hunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f1_hunter.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Not only are the spearmen of the forest experienced hunters with the spear, "
"but they also follow ancient human tradition of taming animals for their "
"advantage. While mostly seen in small groups of wolves, the spearmen can also"
" control all kinds of animals."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Tamer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f2_tamer.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Tamer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Tamer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f2_tamer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Tamers grow with their animals, becoming better at taming them and fighting "
"with them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Trapper, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f2_trapper.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Trapper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Trapper, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f2_trapper.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The forest folk tries to live in harmony with nature and wildlife, but "
"nevertheless, there are those who value profit more.\n"
"Trappers use their tools to capture wild animals and sell them for taming or "
"for their fur.\n"
"\n"
"The traps they set are dangerous for all creatures and can break the leg of a"
" grown man."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f2_trapper.cfg:51
msgid "trap"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Beastmaster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f3_beastmaster.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Beastmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Beastmaster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\f3_beastmaster.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Beastmasters live up to their name. Often accompanied by many different "
"animals, they are able to encorporate their taming ability into their "
"fighting style."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxeman.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Axefighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxeman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Axefighters work as lumberjacks in peaceful times and as a fore to be "
"reckoned with on the battlefield. Strenghtened through their daily work these"
" men can fight on equal ground with trained soldiers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axemaster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxemaster.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Axtmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axemaster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxemaster.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Axemasters carry a big waraxe which they use with astonishing agility. "
"Deadly in close combat these warriors with their precise thrown hatchets "
"shoudn't be underestimated by archers either."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxemaster.cfg:33
msgid "War-axe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axethrower, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxethrower.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Axethrower"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Axethrower, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Forestaxethrower.cfg:16
msgid ""
"A simple tool for every day use and a useful weapon in fights; The axe is the"
" best friend of a forestdweller. Axethrowers have learned the usefulness of "
"the axe in melee and ranged combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Shaman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m1-shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Shaman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m1-shaman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Shamans use forest spirits as source of their magic and can control nature to"
" a certain degree. While their skills have only minor use in combat, they "
"cover a large field of use in daily life."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m2-forest_mage.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m2-forest_mage.cfg:17
msgid ""
"To live in and from the forest without hurting it is hard work. For this the "
"forest mages have learned to take care of the trees and the spirits. Without "
"the balance the peacful live in the forest would surely fail."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Healer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m2-herbalist.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Herbalist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Healer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m2-herbalist.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Herbalist have a vast knowledge of plants and herbs, which they can use to "
"treat illnesses and wounds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Druid, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m3-druid.cfg:4
msgid "Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Druid, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\m3-druid.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Druids are wise men with an incredible skill in nature magic and understandig"
" of nature. They are capable of communicating with the wood spirits and "
"appeasing them.\n"
"\n"
"Additional to bending the forest to their will, druids are adept at all "
"nature magic and can even call lightning from the sky."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear_cub, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t1-bear_cub.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Cub"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear_cub, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t1-bear_cub.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Deep in the forest spiritual magic is still strong, allowing creatures to "
"exist, that have no place elsewhere.Strong spirits control the trees and from"
" bodies out of twigs. Their appearance allows them to blend in perfectly with"
" their natural habitat and they can regenerate themself with nearby wood. If "
"threatend the spirits can attack with all the might of the forest, but they "
"also have a great weakness to fire and magic.\n"
"The weaker ones are called cubs and grow leaves on their back to be able to "
"hide in the forest. They are not easily tamed, but are friendly to those who "
"respect the forest."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t2-bear.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t2-bear.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The back of the magical bear creatures is covered in leaves, so they often "
"appear as bushes. Though they do not often attack on their own it is better "
"not to travel to deep into their territory."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear_spirit, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t3-bear_spirit.cfg:4
msgid "Spirit of the Forest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_bear_spirit, race=monster
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\t3-bear_spirit.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The ancient beings of the forest are called 'Spirit of the Forest' and act as"
" guardians of the woods. They often appear as bears, though they can take on "
"any form of woodland creatures. When in the forest they can hardly be seen, "
"so if you ever feel watched while traveling in the woods remember: The eyes "
"of the Guardians are watching and you better not have angered them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forest_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf.cfg:4
msgid "Forest Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Forest_Wolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Alpha_Wolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Young_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf.cfg:17
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf_great.cfg:18
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf_young.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Wolves are aggressive animals that hunt in packs. Although weak individually,"
" a wolf pack can kill even the strongest man in minutes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Alpha_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf_great.cfg:4
msgid "Alpha Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_fh_Young_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\RE_units\human-forest\Wolf_young.cfg:4
msgid "Young Forest Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Eaglemaster, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-big.cfg:4
msgid "Eaglemaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Eaglemaster, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-big.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Eaglemasters have the abilty to tame and train the largest and most "
"dangerous birds of prey. They are always accompanied by their personal eagle,"
" but they also train the captured Rocs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-big.cfg:43
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-mid.cfg:41
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-small.cfg:41
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Raventrainer.cfg:57
msgid "dive"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Falconmaster, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-mid.cfg:4
msgid "Falconmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Falconmaster, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-mid.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A trained falcon can be dangerous to larger creatures, as it can target "
"vulnerable spots more precisely than an arrow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Falcontrainer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-small.cfg:4
msgid "Falcontrainer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Falcontrainer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Birdtrainer-small.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Birds of prey are valuable for hunting, but can also deliver messages quickly"
" over large distances. The Falcontrainers are esteemed members of their "
"villages, thanks to the usefullness of their student."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Earthgolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-earth.cfg:4
msgid "Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Earthgolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-earth.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Larger than most men and with a skin of stone, the Earthgolems are bulwarks "
"in battle. They are carved out from the mountains and animated by skillful "
"Geomancers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Rockgolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-rock.cfg:4
msgid "Rockgolem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Rockgolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-rock.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Towering as tall as 3 meters, these mobile mountains can brush of most damage"
" or any atempt at slowing them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Stonegolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-stone.cfg:4
msgid "Stonegolem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Stonegolem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Golem-stone.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Over time the Golems take on mass and size by merging with other rocks. "
"Stonegolems hit hard and withstand tremendous ammount of damage. Only arcane "
"magic is a threat to them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Eremit, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Eremit.cfg:4
msgid "Hermit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Eremit, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Eremit.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Hermits seek the solitude and beauty of mountains. They have a vast knowledge"
" on every animal and plant. Some say the earth itself speaks to them. Hermits"
" live a peaceful live, but if anyone thinks they are an easy target they soon"
" will be disproved as they are crushed beneath tons of stones."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Eremit.cfg:51
msgid "avalanche"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Eremit.cfg:63
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wandering.cfg:59
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wise.cfg:63
msgid "stoneshard assault"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wandering.cfg:4
msgid "Wandering Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wandering.cfg:17
msgid ""
"On a Quest for knowledge some Mages travel through the world. They focus on "
"the more practical side of magic, moving stones out of their way or flinging "
"them at rouges who try to waylay helpless wanderers. To protect themself "
"against the forces of nature Wandering Mages wear fire and cold resistant "
"robes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wise, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wise.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Wise"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wise, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wise.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A wise man would draw knowledge from many different sources, which is why "
"these mages are not only expert magicians, but able healers as well."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Mage_Wise.cfg:51
msgid "rockfall"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Raventrainer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Raventrainer.cfg:4
msgid "Raventrainer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Raventrainer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=female
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Raventrainer.cfg:34
msgid ""
"When the lights start to fade and parents bring their kids to bed, they tell "
"the bad children dark tales before sleep. A gruesome one, based on a real "
"events, is the legend of Karasu the Raventrainer.Before Karasu was born a "
"seer came to her parents to warn them of the child. The seer had foreseen how"
" vicious and cruel Karasu would be and convinced the father to kill the child"
" as soon as it was born. In a stormy night, while the father was out hunting,"
" the mother was in labor and after few hours the baby was born. The mother "
"fell in love with her child and decided to protect it from its father. So she"
" packed the baby in linen and fled into the night, even though she was still "
"in a weakened state.\n"
"A few hours later the father returned and was furious when the maid told him "
"what happened. He took his dog and crossbow and went after the runaways. Soon"
" the dog had tracked down the two near a mountain cliff. The mad father shot "
"a bolt right through the mother heart, who colappsed in an instant. Taking "
"his knife from his belt the man approached the crying baby to finish what "
"he'd done, but an unkindness of ravens appeared on the sky and plunged on the"
" two hunters. In few second the birds had completely mangled them to a point,"
" where it was hard to tell which body was man and which dog.It is unknown "
"what happened in the next years. Some say Karasu was found and raised by a "
"traveller, in the most common theory she was raised by wild animals.About a "
"decade later stories where heard about a girl in the wilds, who traines birds"
" for hunting. Many had looked for her, some claim to have spotted her from a "
"distance, but anyone who had approached the maiden was never to be seen "
"again.At dusk, when Karasu was about twenty years old, she appeared in her "
"home village with 13 ravens. She didn't speak a word, only stood there as if "
"she was waiting for something. Then, when the sun was gone, the ravens "
"screamed and fell upon the villagers. More birds began to appear and they "
"clawed and pecked on the villagers faces, while the they could only flee in "
"panic. Soon everything was silent again, exept for the sounds as Karasu and "
"her birds feasted on the corpses. Before the sun could rise again the bodies "
"were plucked dry to the bone.Though Karasu never attacked any other villages,"
" lone travellers often dissapear on her mountain and there are many stories "
"about the ravengirl."
msgstr ""

#. [swarm]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Raventrainer.cfg:64
msgid "swarm 5"
msgstr ""

#. [swarm]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Raventrainer.cfg:65
msgid "The more wounded this unit is the less attacks they get, to the minimum of 5"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Roc, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc.cfg:4
msgid "Roc"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Roc, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Roc's are gigantic birds that can dive to the ground at impressive speeds. "
"Any traveller in the mountains should be aware of these beasts and know how "
"to hide from them if they want to survive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Thunderbird, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc_thunder.cfg:4
msgid "Thunderbird"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Thunderbird, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc_thunder.cfg:17
msgid ""
"These massive birds are often accompanied by storms, though it is unclear if "
"they use the dark skies to hide of if they conjure the wind themself with a "
"flap of their wings."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Roc_small, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc_young.cfg:4
msgid "Young Roc"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Roc_small, race=AE_RHY_roc
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Roc_young.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Even when leaving the nest, these birds have an impressive size and claws "
"sharp enough to kill a cow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Adventurer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Adventurer.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Adventurer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Adventurer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Adventurer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Master survivalist and fearsome foes to bandits; The Adventurers are "
"unmatched by any other human in scouting as well as conquering terrain that "
"was deemed unhabitable. Their alpenstock can be used as multitool for hunting"
" and climbing and the adventurers have learned to cripple prey with a precise"
" throw of their boomerang."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Adventurer.cfg:39
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Adventurer.cfg:48
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Explorer.cfg:36
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Explorer.cfg:45
msgid "alpenstock"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Adventurer.cfg:57
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Explorer.cfg:54
msgid "boomerang"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Explorer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Explorer.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Explorer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Explorer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Explorer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Explorer clear the paths for human settlements. With experience in scouting "
"and hunting they are the first to enter unexplored terrain. Not everyone "
"survives those dangerous trips, but thanks to these brave men, the borders of"
" civilisation is ever growing.The alpenstock is an amazing invention that "
"aids them along their travels. The top end acts as grip for walking, but can "
"also be used for climbing and for self defense. The lower end is still pointy"
" enough to act as an emergency spear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Hunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Hunter.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Hunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Hunter.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Hunters are expert survivalists, having both knowledge about dangers in the "
"mountains, as well as the ability to hunt wildlife for meat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Ranger.cfg:17
msgid "Thanks to their equipment, Rangers can easily traverse in snow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Traveller, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Traveller.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Traveller"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Traveller, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Traveller.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Travellers can take a variety of jobs in their village. Often they transport "
"goods and messages across long distances on paths no one else would use. "
"Though not particular strong, they know how to survive in the wilderness and "
"defend against wild animals and bandits.They often carry a knife for basic "
"utilities, but the real weapon is their sling and the sharp end of their "
"walking stick."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Scout_Traveller.cfg:45
msgid "walking stick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Flareman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Watcher_Flareman.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Flareman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Flareman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Watcher_Flareman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A Flareman not only acts for signaling, but is a trained guard as well, "
"delaying the enemy until reinforcements arrive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Signalman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Watcher_Signalman.cfg:4
msgid "Mountain Signalman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Signalman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Watcher_Signalman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Travelling distances in the mountain regions would delay any important "
"message, which is why these signalmen learned how to transfer messages with "
"their torches, which can be seen from far away."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolfguard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfguard.cfg:4
msgid "Wolfguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolfguard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfguard.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Wolfguards have takes a more defensive appoach to battle, though thier skills"
" with the sword is nothing to be dismissed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolfchampion, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfm_champ.cfg:4
msgid "Wolfchampion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolf_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfm_fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolf_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfm_fighter.cfg:16
msgid "As a signal of strength, warriors often wear the hide of slayed beasts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolf_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfm_warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolf_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfm_warrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"These warriors are so fearless and agressive, people have speculated if they "
"are even human anymore."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_mh_Wolfswordmaster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-mountain\Wolfswordmaster.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Swordmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The use of archery in shooting something other than game was seen from its "
"inception, and archers have been indispensable in warfare since time "
"immemorial. Usually of humble origins, hailing from the peasantry or "
"woodsmen, military bowmen are trained to competence with both a bow and a "
"short sword, and are very common on the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Master_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Master Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Master_Bowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Master.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Master bowmen have reached the zenith of their art, inasmuch as any human is "
"capable. Armed with both a sword, and a great yew bow, these warriors crown "
"battalions of archers with their presence, bringing down many a foe with "
"their well-aimed shots. Their skill with the sword is also not to be "
"discounted; they are easily as good with it as any novice swordsman. Of the "
"many races in the world, only the elves surpass humanity in archery, and "
"their human counterparts have speculated, perhaps in envy, that this is only "
"by dint of age."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Ranger, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_ranger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Rangers wear lighter equipment in order to move fast in terrain. If they are "
"employed in the army they often act in a scouting role, and have to be "
"reliable at day and night. Instead of a unwieldy longbow, they use shorter "
"compound bows, that lack the punch, but are more accurate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Knight_Errant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Errant.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Knight Errant"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Errant.cfg:29
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Errant.cfg:38
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Wander.cfg:27
msgid "warhammer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Nobleman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Noble.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Mounted Nobleman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Traveling_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Cav_Wander.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Traveling Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Champion, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horse_Champion.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Tourney Champion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Champion, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horse_Champion.cfg:19
msgid ""
"It is said these noble knights slay Dragons by themself, beat back whole "
"armies single handely and have felled hundreds of evil knights.\n"
"\t\n"
"Incidentally they are more seen on tourneys than anywhere on the battlefield,"
" but are you really going to argue with their fanbase?"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_King, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\King.cfg:4
msgid "Regis King"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_King, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\King.cfg:29
msgid ""
"King Gerald IV is an ambitioned leader. He hits hard with his mighty war-mace"
" and the magical enhanced crown jewels allow him to rain fire upon his "
"enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\King.cfg:43
msgid "warmace"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Noble_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\L1_baron.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Baron"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Noble_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\L1_baron.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Barons belong to the lower end of nobility. Thanks to their privilege they "
"can afford good education and training in martial arts and etiquette. Unlike "
"the common soldier, they prefer the skillful art of fencing.\n"
"Their armor is light not inhibit their movement, but does not offer much "
"protection either. Additional to their saber, they equip a light crossbow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Noble_Commander, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\L2_earl.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Earl"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Noble_Commander, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\L2_earl.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Earls do enjoy high education in the fields of war, and are best suited in "
"fashioning battleplans and leading their army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Noble_Lord, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\L3_duke.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Duke"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Humans have often pondered the workings of the world in which they live. Some"
" endeavor to take this beyond idle musing, to set it as the primary "
"enterprise of their lives. Any magi worthy of the title have spent at least a"
" decade in study, amassing a sum of knowledge which sets them apart from "
"other people. These men and women, who have committed themselves fully to the"
" pursuit of wisdom, stand in stark contrast to a world where few can even "
"read and write. Their ranks are filled with the children of hopeful nobility,"
" or those who sought an escape from the intellectual void of manual labor.It "
"is an irony that, with all their knowledge, and their unassuming monopoly "
"thereof, the collective community of magi could likely rule society, were "
"they ever to try. However, their true love is neither money, nor power, and "
"those who see the study of magic as a means to such ends often lack the very "
"conviction required for true mastery.Physically frail, and lacking "
"familiarity with combat, magi do possess certain arts which are of great "
"utility in battle."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage.cfg:89
msgid "female^Regis Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Red_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage2_High.cfg:4
msgid "Regis High Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Red_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage2_High.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Upon the successful culmination of their apprenticeship, a mage is stripped "
"of the brown robes of an apprentice and given the ruddy cloak of a master. "
"The significance of this change is often lost on the peasantry, who "
"mistakenly title Master Magi as ‘Red Magi’. Likewise, the symbolism of the "
"change in colors is often mistaken to signify the mage’s ability to seemingly"
" conjure fire from nothing but thin air, a trick which, although undeniably "
"useful, is viewed by the magi themselves as a crass application of their "
"hard-won knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Though physically frail, and untrained as warriors, the ‘Red Magi’ have a "
"number of tricks up their sleeves, including the gouts of fire which may have"
" cemented their colloquial name."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage2_High.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Compared to other mages, Red Mages have a higher resistance to ‘fire’ "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage2_High.cfg:97
msgid "female^Regis High Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Arch_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage3_Court.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Court Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Arch_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage3_Court.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The title of Arch Mage is traditionally conferred only after a lifetime of "
"study and achievement to match. Arch Magi are often employed in positions of "
"education, or as advisors to those sensible enough to seek the fruits of "
"their wisdom. Many tend to wealthy patrons, a profitable enterprise for both "
"as, outside of the occasional thaumaturgy or word of advice, it gives the "
"mage leave to pursue their research undisturbed. From this flows the greater "
"body of human knowledge; the sciences, the philosophies, and the arts which "
"give beauty to the world at large.\n"
"\n"
"Though not trained for any sort of combat, if need arises an Arch Mage can "
"unleash the full power of their art, something which is not to be taken "
"lightly."
msgstr ""

