#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Black_Paladin, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Black_Paladin.cfg:4
msgid "Black Paladin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Black_Paladin, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Black_Paladin.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Even the strongest knight can fall under an evil curse. Black Paladins were "
"once devoted servants of good, but were raised again after their death to "
"join the undead army. Stripped of their soul they can only obey their new "
"lord. The Black Paladins keep the strenght they had and all blessings, which "
"shielded their body against arcane forces. Even the purifying spells, they "
"once learned in life, can be used in their new form."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Death_Knight, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Death_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Death Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Death_Knight, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Death_Knight.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Tales are told of the mightiest warriors and generals, who, cursed with hate "
"and stung by betrayal, have come back to this world as Death Knights. "
"Wielding the same weapons as in life, they command the Undead in their quest "
"for revenge."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Death_Squire, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Death_Squire.cfg:4
msgid "Death Squire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Death_Squire, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Death_Squire.cfg:39
msgid ""
"There are certainly undead creatures that are more terrifying than these "
"humanoid skeletons, but there's something specific to an tireless, "
"intelligent being that defies death."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Junker, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Junker.cfg:4
msgid "Skeleton Junker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Junker, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Skele_Junker.cfg:34
msgid ""
"If the Necromancer takes a careful approach of reanimating, the corpse "
"retains some of its abilities from the previous live. These Undead are more "
"intelligent and can act without their masters influence, but they are also "
"harder to control."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_leviathan, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\water_leviathan.cfg:4
msgid "Undead Leviathan"
msgstr ""

